## Learned User Preferences

- Light tasks (docs, preview, dev-mode renders) must NEVER declare `dependsOn` for heavy build targets (multi-min WASM rebuilds) in `project.json` — opening docs should serve whatever artefact is available, not silently trigger a fresh bindgen/WASM build.

## Learned Workspace Facts

- Frontmatter docs validation runs via `pnpm docs:validate` (Nx target `scripts:validate-frontmatter`) over ~280 docs in `docs/policy/` + `docs/research/` — frontmatter `title` must match the H1 byte-for-byte (including backticks/code spans) and an `updated:` field older than 180 days emits a warning; reference-category docs that snapshot upstream sources are exempt by convention but the validator currently still flags them, so bump the `updated:` after a content review or extend the validator to skip `category: 'reference'`. Nx daemon can cache a stale failed project graph from a transient plugin-worker startup timeout (verbose logs show the worker subscription retrying ~8 times before connecting; `./tools/pkgcheck.plugin.ts` and `@nx/react/router-plugin` are the usual victims when spawned last) — `pnpm exec nx reset` clears the daemon and the cached failure; setting `NX_PLUGIN_NO_TIMEOUTS=true` (combine with `NX_DAEMON=false NX_VERBOSE_LOGGING=true` for diagnosis) bypasses the worker startup timeout in one-off invocations. Hybrid oxlint + ESLint linting: oxlint runs first, ESLint handles residual rules; custom Oxlint JS plugins in `libs/oxlint/`; tsgolint (typescript-go) provides type-aware JSDoc codeblock checking via `source_overrides`; rule tests use `oxlint-disable` syntax (ESLint 9 RuleTester strips `eslint-disable` from `getAllComments()`); when only oxlint flags a rule, prefer `oxlint-disable` form — `eslint-disable` for those same names produces "unused directive" warnings since the two linters use divergent rule IDs (e.g. oxlint `no-empty-function` vs ESLint plugin variants); ESLint plugin rules require the plugin prefix in disable directives (e.g. `no-barrel-files/no-barrel-files`, not bare `no-barrel-files`); `oxlint-disable-next-line` only suppresses one line — use block-level `oxlint-disable`/`enable` for sections with multiple violations; tsgolint requires absolute paths — JSDoc codeblock virtualPath must be resolved against the workspace root when `context.filename` is `<input>` (RuleTester default); MDX parser exported separately at `@taucad/oxlint/mdx-parser` (not a property of the ESLint plugin object); `validate-mdx-links` checks internal dead links (relative + absolute, including Fumadocs route groups); `validate-mdx-external-links` checks remote URLs via subprocess with disk cache at `node_modules/.cache/tau-lint/external-links.json`; generated report artifacts under `apps/api/reports/` and tsdown-built `scripts/dist/` must be added to `.oxfmtrc.json` ignore (otherwise format runs keep re-flagging generated TS); workspace `no-restricted-imports` rule prohibits sibling-relative imports (`./foo.js`) — every package and kernel must use `#`-prefixed subpath imports; husky `commit-msg` hook validates scope across `apps/`, `packages/`, `libs/`, AND `kernels/` (kernels added when openscad was extracted); GitHub Actions must use Node-24-compatible action versions (`actions/cache`, `actions/setup-node`, `nrwl/nx-set-shas`) — `.github/actions/setup-nx/action.yml` is the canonical place to bump SHAs; running `pnpm nx test ui app/routes/projects_.$id/...` shell-expands `$id` to empty (the segment is read as a shell variable) and silently runs the wrong path — from `apps/ui` use `pnpm exec vitest --run 'app/routes/projects_.$id/<file>.test.tsx'` with the path quoted so the literal `$id` is preserved
